The Wedding Cake House (formally known as the Kendrick-Prentice-Tirocchi house), is a three-story historic house located at 514 Broadway Street in the Broadway-Armory Historic District of Providence, Rhode Island. Built in 1867 and occupied continuously until 1989, its contents were the subject of a 2001 exhibit at the Rhode Island School of Design Museum. It has had a variety of restoration work conducted since 2011. Photo by @seaofsteps

node.text:
The Armour–Stiner House is one of the most visually distinctive homes in the world. It is a unique octagon-shaped and domed Victorian-style house located at 45 West Clinton Avenue in Irvington, in Westchester County, New York. It was designated a National Historic Landmark in 1976. It is the only known fully domed octagonal residence and the only house modeled after Donato Bramante’s 1502 Tempietto in Rome. The elegantly proportioned Tempietto was built in the form of a Tholos, an ancient classical temple. The Armour–Stiner House reflects America’s fascination with classical forms in the third quarter of the 19th century. Photo from their page, check it out for more @armourstiner

node.text:
9 Walnut Ave, Cambridge, MA 02140
$7,500,000, 6 bd, 6 ba, 7,413 sqft

See this historic Preservation Award-winning grand Victorian home located in Cambridge's Avon Hill neighborhood. Walk into the magnificent entryway and see an ornate hand-carved cherry wood staircase and original stained-glass windows. This home features a recent museum-quality restoration and addition that incorporates old architectural details with modern luxury amenities. Features include a luxury chef's kitchen with Viking and Sub-Zero appliances, a large formal dining room perfect for entertaining, a hydro-air system with remote chillers, a Sonos A/V system, radiant bathroom flooring, and elevator access to four floors. Additional features include a top-floor cupola with wraparound exterior deck and Cambridge skyline views, a fully finished basement with media and exercise rooms, a separate in-law suite with elevator access, an internet-accessible security system, a slate roof with copper flashing, and a heated driveway/sidewalk with brick pavers that leads to a 2-car garage

Listed by:
Adam Kotkin
Red Tree Real Estate

node.text:
1314 Addison St, Berkeley, CA 94702
$1,895,000, 4 bd, 3 ba, 2,205 sqft

Prepare to be wowed by this Berkeley Victorian’s transformation into a sleek, modern abode. The juxtaposition of ultra-contemporary interior design + restored vintage elements enjoy a happy marriage in this Poet’s Corner home just steps from beloved Strawberry Creek Park. Originally built in 1898 and completely renovated from the foundation up since 2016. There is space for everyone with 4 bedrooms, a flex space, 3 full bathrooms, and an easy flow from the living to dining areas and into the dream kitchen featuring Wolf, Sub Zero, and Bosch appliances. The back of the home opens to an enviable low maintenance backyard with an outdoor soaking tub + uber cool play structure. The bedrooms are spacious and all 3 bathrooms are beyond well equipped. The primary suite is a perfect retreat with its marble bath + walk-in closet. Around every corner you’ll find insta-worthy lighting, wallcoverings, + finishes. Visiting this house is a special event but calling it home will be an everlasting joy.

node.text:
657 Highland Ave, Fall River, MA 02720
$1,200,000, 6 bd, 3 ba, 4,577 sqft

Located in the Highlands, The Rising Sun,  An innovative Japanese-influenced residential design by Ralph Adams Cram, an INFLUENCER of Frank Lloyd Wright.  Cram’s design of the Rising Sun is a seminal Japanese Arts and Crafts house listed on the Massachusetts Historic Register. Situated on a ½ acre,  this uniquely charming home was built in 1894 with exacting attention to detail. This notable historic house has many features as well as future possibilities.  Beamed ceilings, beautiful woodwork, a skylighted central staircase, 4 working fireplaces, home offices on both the 2nd and 3rd floors, as well as 6 bedrooms . Hardwood floors throughout the home, a Japanese teahouse, and signed carved wooden panels, are just a few of the features of this intriguing home.  Constructed by the  Japanese technique  known as KANAWA TSUGI which doesn't use nails but bonds wood to wood.  It is built so well that the original solid Walnut doors still exist over 127 years.

Listed by:
David Durot
Century 21 Topsail Realty - Newport

node.text:
301 Main Street, Oxford Alabama, 36203
$274,900, 6 bd, 5 ba, 5,271 sqft

This downtown Oxford home will captivate you with its beauty and history. As one of the only properties in Alabama listed on the national historic registry, its charm and character has been preserved over the last century. As you walk through the home you will visualize the narrative told about the life of a family at the turn of the century. Included in these features is the genuine copper fountain and basin used by Annie Cooper to water her ferns, the original kitchen with authentic 1800's appliances and components and bathrooms with cast iron claw foot tub and fixtures installed at the origin of indoor plumbing. In addition to the house the property contains three other historic resources. A recreational building to the rear of the house contains a rare box ball alley, a precursor to a modern bowling alley, the only one known of in the state of Alabama, a gazebo built in the early 1900's constructed from the branches of trees and a brick garage.

Listed By:
Karl Heckman
eXp Realty, LLC Central
